                    <msContents>
                        <summary>An undated, complete abridgement of a Persian treatise entitled
                                <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Riyāz̤ al-Maẕāhib</title> (Garden of
                            Religions), by <persName>Panḍit Māthurā Nāth Brahman Mālvī</persName>,
                            Librarian of the Hindu College at Benares (Varanasi). Originally
                            composed in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1812">1228 AH (1812
                                CE)</date>. In his introduction, he describes how <persName>John
                                Glynn</persName>, then Benares City Registrar, inspired him to
                            prepare a survey of Indian religions. However, since the author of this
                            volume explicitly mentions both <persName role="subject">William
                                Augustus Brooke (1784–1833)</persName>, who long lived and ultimated
                            died in Benares, as well as <persName role="subject">William Wilberforce
                                Bird (1784-1857)</persName>, appointed Judge and Magistrate of
                            Benares in 1814, then promoted to Commissioner, 1826–1829. Therefore,
                            the completion of this abridgment likely dates to the latter's
                            tenure.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_956-item1">
                            <author role="scr" key="person_7064232"
                                ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/7064232/">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Panḍit Māthurā Nāth Brahman
                                    Mālvī</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">پندٹ متهرا ناتهه برهمن مالوی</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22388">Riyāz̤
                                al-Maẕāhib</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar">ریاض المذاهب</title>
                            <incipit><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus> حمدی که
                                سزاوار بر حـق بـود از کمترین ممکنات کجا اداد شود آری بیت‌ حادث بقدیم
                                کی برد راه‌ کتان زکـجا و پرتـو ماه... </incipit>
                            <explicit><locus from="77b" to="77b"> برگ ۷۷پ (folio 77b):</locus> که
                                هستی را نمیدانم بقای * مکر صاحبدلی روزی برحمت‌. کـند در‌ کار این
                                مسکین دعـایی الله بـس و ما بقی هوس تمام شد تـم ‌تم‌ تم. </explicit>
                            <colophon>Uninformative colophon.</colophon>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>

                            <note><persName>Horace Hayman Wilson</persName> principally references
                                this work in his 'Sketch of the religious sects of the
                                Hindus'.</note>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
